description:
Hand of Glory’ is a cosy and beautiful pub from JaguarShoes Collective… Its theme celebrates pagan festivals, traditional iconography and folkloric customs from across the history of the British Isles.

The pub is sited at the original ‘Amhurst’ pub and holds a liquor license dating back to the 1800’s when the surrounding area was primarily fields and farmland.

Focusing a roster of ales and beers and countryside ciders from some of the UK’s best independent brewers. Hand of Glory pub was an early pioneer in the new wave or craft brewing and features a range of constantly rotating ales and a menu of potent, small batch ’Deadly Ciders’. Alongside this there’s rustic Bloody Mary’s, cocktails and a menu of infused ‘Seven Deadly Gins.’

description:
Bell and Viv is a special cocktail bar and restaurant inspired by the classic European café that fosters the community and encourages people to come together for drinks, food, and fun.
We offer a casual environment where people can drop by for our speciality coffee, enjoy a bite to eat for breakfast, lunch or dinner, relax after work with a refreshing cocktail or on the weekends to unwind. Our goal is to create a warm and welcoming space where people can come together and enjoy good company. Our hidden basement cocktail parlour, The Drinks Trolley, is perfect for intimate gatherings with friends.
Looking to visit us on the weekend? We offer a Bottomless Brunch on Saturdays.

description:
Established in 1805. A Chapel Market staple for over two hundred years. The Chapel Market Tavern is situated at the Western end of one of London’s oldest street markets.

We take pride in offering the very best of locally sourced ingredients to deliver a delicious menu of homemade pub classics – including a fantastic traditional roast every Sunday.

To accompany our food we have fifteen draft beer lines that regularly rotate to showcase the very best from the UK craft beer scene, a carefully curated wine list and a back bar packed with a variety of specialist spirits.

The Chapel Market Tavern comes from the same team behind Ninth Ward in Clerkenwell, the Temple of Foo in St Paul’s and the George & Monkey in Angel.

description:
DRINK. DINE. DANCE.

Step into The Cross, an iconic London venue reborn. Once famed for '90s raves under King’s Cross railway arches, it’s now a six-storey hub of dining, drinking, and dancing.
The Cross features a ground-floor bar, a stylish restaurant, a cocktail lounge, and a rooftop terrace with breathtaking views of London. Perfect for every occasion, it serves as a cocktail bar, restaurant, wedding venue, corporate venue hire, private dining, and group dining spot.
On weekends, it transforms into the ultimate nightlife destination. Whether for pre-drinks, after-parties, or celebrations, The Cross promises an unforgettable experience.

description:
Hidden beneath Happy Face pizzeria, SUPERMAX is a basement bar heavy on the cocktails, neon lights and sound system, serving vermouth-led drinks and cicchetti until the small hours every night from Wednesday to Saturday.

POST-WORK DRINKS: APERITIVO HOUR
Shake off the working day and head to SUPERMAX for Aperitivo Hour from 5:30–7pm, which sees £6 cocktails on offer alongside a selection of delicious cicchetti.

DJs AT SUPERMAX
Dancefloor action in King's Cross! Friday and Saturday nights at SUPERMAX are all about the party with DJs from the Spiritland camp playing on a big sound system with the lights down and disco balls spinning. Entrance is free.

PRIVATE HIRE
Want the place to yourself? Get in touch: events@supermaxbar.com
